But this kind of approach is not a good as per industry standards. Hence, use can try using `@classmethod` decorator 

    class Book:
        def __init__(self, title, author, pages):
            self.title = title
            self.author = author
            self.pages = pages
    
        @classmethod
        def from_json(cls, book_as_json):
        	book = json.loads(book_as_json)
        	return cls(title=book[&#39;title&#39;], author=book[&#39;author&#39;], pages=book[&#39;pages&#39;])


